      "location": "header",
      "position": "before",
      "content": "## Overview\n\nArcade.dev LLM tools for Microsoft OneDrive that enable LLM-driven workflows to manage OneDrive content and metadata programmatically. The toolkit exposes common OneDrive operations for files, folders, sharing, search, and user/drive queries.\n\n**Capabilities**\n\n- File and folder management: create folders, copy, move, and delete items; list folder contents (root if omitted).\n- Sharing and access: create share links and list items shared with the current user.\n- Search and discovery: search the user's OneDrive (note: index updates may take seconds to minutes).\n- Metadata and account info: retrieve drive metadata and current user/OneDrive context (GetMyDrive, WhoAmI).\n- Async operation monitoring: check status of long-running copy operations via the provided monitor URL.\n\n**OAuth**\n\n- Provider: microsoft\n- Required scopes: Files.Read, Files.ReadWrite, User.Read\n\nTokens must include the listed scopes so the toolkit can read and modify files and access basic user/drive information."
    }
  ],
